 Autonomous Quote Agents
The Problem
Traditional auto insurance quoting is often a bottleneck. Underwriters are overwhelmed by manual reviews, and sales agents lose potential customers due to slow response times or rigid pricing. Most systems are either "dumb" (simple rule-sets) or "black boxes" (ML models that humans don't trust).
The Solution
Built during a 48-hour hackathon with a team of friends, Autonomous Quote Agents is a multi-agent AI orchestration system designed to automate the end-to-end insurance lifecycle.
By breaking down the quoting process into four specialized AI agents, we’ve created a system that doesn't just predict outcomes—it reasons through them. It profiles risk, predicts the likelihood of a sale (binding), suggests premium adjustments to stay competitive, and decides whether to approve the quote instantly or escalate it to a human underwriter.
🧠 The Agentic Architecture
Our system moves away from a single monolithic model and instead uses a "Chain-of-Thought" Pipeline:
Agent 1: The Risk Profiler (The Underwriter)
Uses a Random Forest (200 trees) to categorize the applicant into risk tiers. It handles class imbalance via balanced weighting to ensure high-risk drivers aren't missed.
Agent 2: The Conversion Predictor (The Sales Lead)
Powered by a Gradient Boosting Machine (GBM), this agent analyzes historical bind data (146k+ records) to predict the probability that a user will actually purchase the policy.
Agent 3: The Premium Advisor (The Negotiator)
A hybrid agent that combines ML insights with domain-specific logic. It suggests premium discounts or "sweet spots" to increase conversion without compromising the loss ratio.
Agent 4: Decision Router (The Manager)
The final gatekeeper. It evaluates the confidence levels and outputs of the previous three agents to decide the final action: Auto-Approve, Agent Follow-Up, or Underwriter Escalation.
✨ Key Innovations
Handling Imbalance: Insurance data is notoriously imbalanced (only 22% of quotes usually "bind"). We implemented custom sample weighting and balanced class weights to ensure our models are sensitive to successful conversions.
Explainable AI (XAI): We built a "Chain-of-Thought" logging system. Every quote processed shows exactly why an agent made a decision, providing a plain-English audit trail for human supervisors.
Confidence-Based Routing: The system doesn't just guess; it knows when it's unsure. If Agent 1's confidence drops below 50%, the system automatically flags the quote for human intervention.
Scale: Validated on a massive dataset of 146,259 records, proving the system can handle enterprise-level quote volumes.
🛠️ Built With
Python / Flask: Core backend and web dashboard.
Scikit-Learn: Machine learning models (RandomForest & GradientBoosting).
Pandas & NumPy: High-performance data processing for 146k+ records.
Custom Agent Orchestration: Our proprietary logic for passing state between the four specialized agents.
